{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567095","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567095"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:54:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:54:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18932"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18932","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18932"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.91,0.03,0.04,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11666"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112700"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11666","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11666"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18932"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94733"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"2429"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5644"},{"type":"tags","id":"5741"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11346"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27451"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27452"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46186"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112700","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/112700"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student is completing their surgical rotation. Their supervisor frequently makes them stay back after hours to complete administrative tasks unrelated to their learning objectives. The supervisor tells the student that doing these extra tasks will result in better assessment grades.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes why this supervision arrangement is inappropriate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Inadequate documentation of feedback","Misuse of power differential for personal benefit","Failure to provide structured learning opportunities","Breach of duty to prioritise student education","Lack of formal assessment criteria"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe key issue in this scenario is the \u003Cstrong\u003Emisuse of power differential for personal benefit\u003C/strong\u003E. The supervisor is exploiting their position of authority by linking administrative tasks to assessment outcomes, which is unprofessional and potentially coercive. This violates the principle that teachers and supervisors must not take advantage of the inherent power imbalance in educational relationships.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFailure to provide structured learning opportunities\u003C/strong\u003E - While important, this is not the primary ethical concern in this scenario\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBreach of duty to prioritise student education\u003C/strong\u003E - The issue is not about assessment structure but about inappropriate use of assessment power\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInadequate documentation of feedback\u003C/strong\u003E - While the supervisor\u0027s behaviour shows poor planning, this is not the main ethical issue\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELack of formal assessment criteria\u003C/strong\u003E - The primary concern is the abuse of power, not documentation practices\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMedical supervisors have a responsibility to maintain professional boundaries and ensure that their teaching and assessment practices are fair, transparent, and focused on student learning rather than personal benefit.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Medical supervisors have a responsibility to provide adequate oversight and feedback to students while maintaining professional boundaries.","Power imbalances between supervisors and students must be recognised and managed appropriately.","Effective clinical teaching requires clear communication and respect for learner wellbeing."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","AMSA Code of Ethics. In Australian medical student association [online]. Available at: https://amsa.org.au/advocacy-and-policy/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94733"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18932"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94733","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/94733"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-04T08:24:41+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-04T08:26:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11666"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112700"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{